  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.35 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-16.7B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+20.3B), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging zone but leaning toward selling pressure as spot approaches the 6605 resistance wall. The PIN regime with 2.8B total GEX suggests dealers will provide liquidity by selling any push toward 6605-6610 and buying dips toward 6590, creating a tight trading range. Key levels to watch are the 6590 support (where dealer buying accelerates) and 6605 resistance (where dealer selling intensifies), with the gex_surge event indicating heightened hedging activity that should compress volatility within this 15-point corridor.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with limited breakout potential.",
